<div
	class="box-border flex h-full min-h-0 flex-col overflow-y-auto overflow-x-hidden bg-page p-8 text-ink"
	style="min-height: 100%; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;"
>
	<p class="font-sans text-[10px] font-medium tracking-[0.25em] text-muted uppercase">
		In her words
	</p>
	<p class="mt-1 font-sans text-[10px] text-muted">Continued</p>

	<div class="mt-6 space-y-6 font-sans">
		<div class="space-y-2">
			<p class="text-left text-sm font-bold leading-snug text-ink">
				Who’s your favorite model or biggest inspiration?
			</p>
			<blockquote class="m-0 border-0 p-0 text-left text-xs leading-relaxed text-ink/90">
				<span class="font-serif text-[1.05em] text-ink/70">“</span>I would say Barbara Palvin—not only because she’s stunning, but also because of her character. She’s so cheerful, funny, loyal, and I just love that about her (and she watches anime, too).<span class="font-serif text-[1.05em] text-ink/70">”</span>
			</blockquote>
		</div>
		<div class="space-y-2">
			<p class="text-left text-sm font-bold leading-snug text-ink">
				Are there any brands or designers you’d love to represent or walk for?
			</p>
			<blockquote class="m-0 border-0 p-0 text-left text-xs leading-relaxed text-ink/90">
				<span class="font-serif text-[1.05em] text-ink/70">“</span>Victoria’s Secret—since I was a kid I’ve loved pretending I’m wearing the wings and walking the school corridors like everyone’s watching. The feeling is unmatched!<span class="font-serif text-[1.05em] text-ink/70">”</span>
			</blockquote>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
